at the National Central Library.

114
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:27,800
If you pass the test, you can get 
materials that will give you dozens—

115
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:31,130
no, hundreds of times 
more knowledge than this.

116
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:32,810
Is that right?

117
00:05:33,380 --> 00:05:35,250
Brother, we should get busy—

118
00:05:39,620 --> 00:05:41,100
Oh, Brother...

119
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:46,820
Ed-kun, are you making any progress with your studies?

120
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:48,740
Yeah, some.

121
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:51,330
But there's so much stuff here that I didn't know.

122
00:05:51,770 --> 00:05:56,200
The test is hard even for adults who have received special education.

123
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,680
But you're still so young.

124
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,820
You don't need to force yourself to 
worry about it this year.

125
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:01,750
No...

126
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:04,580
I'll try to do everything that I can,

127
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:07,840
