possibilities are of me passing.

128
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:10,650
If I can keep moving ahead...

129
00:06:12,050 --> 00:06:15,890
Bigger Brother, 
you haven't eaten anything!

130
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:19,140
That won't do! You have to make sure to eat!

131
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:21,470
Huh? Um...

132
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:24,650
Thanks.

133
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:26,950
This sure does look delicious.

134
00:06:26,950 --> 00:06:28,650
Be sure you chew it well!

135
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,420
Mm-hmm.

136
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:32,160
This sure is good!

137
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,410
Here! Have another one!

138
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:39,420
Can't sleep?

139
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:43,420
Yeah. My head is too full of all the things I learned.

140
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:44,670
Oh, yeah?

141
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,830
Say, Brother...

142
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:51,160
I'm sure you'll be able 
to pass the test.

143
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,750
So you should at least get a good night's rest.

144
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:58,300
It sure takes me back, the way this all feels.

145
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:04,730
The two of us wanted nothing 
but to become State Alchemists.

146
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:09,700
Once we did, we felt that some kind of path would become open to us.

147
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:18,250
Oh no, is it this late already?

148
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:22,000
Al, where are you?

149
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,700
Is he off playing?

150
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:29,350
Al!

151
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,840
Brother!

152
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:34,550
Little Big Brother, it snowed!

153
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,950
Big Brothers,

154
00:07:55,210 --> 00:07:59,450
I wish you could stay here all the time 
after you pass your test.

155
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:08,300
Big Brother, what are you drawing?

156
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:10,700
It's called a transmutation circle.

157
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,510
It's an incantation to get a wish granted.

158
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:14,260
All right!

159
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,070
Watch this!

160
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:26,900
Incredible! Big Brother, 
that was amazing!

161
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,300
Not bad!

162
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:31,080
Major Hughes!

163
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:33,680
Hey there! I've come to pick you up.

164
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,360
It's your birthday today, right, Ed?

165
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,480
Now that you mention it...

166
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:40,330
How would you know 
something like that?

167
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:43,270
I <i>am</i> with the research department, you know.

168
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:45,750
Come on, let's go to my house. My wife is waiting.

169
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,670
You too there, little lady.

170
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,170
A celebration is more fun 
if you share it with everyone!

171
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,180
Come on in!

172
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:59,380
Thank you all for coming.

173
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:00,760
This is my wife, Gracia.

174
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,100
Your stomach's so big!

175
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,200
Oh, my goodness!

176
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:05,350
You're going to have a baby?

177
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:06,720
Very shortly now.

178
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:10,480
There's a big fuss inside my tummy saying "I want to come out soon!"

179
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,000
Really?

180
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:12,990
Do you want to feel?

181
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,520
N-No!

182
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,990
Nina wants to feel!

183
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,070
Go ahead, Nina-chan.

184
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:21,990
It moved!

185
00:09:22,260 --> 00:09:24,050
Incredible! Incredible!

186
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:38,720
Okay then, does anyone want refills on their tea?

187
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:40,800
Oh, thanks!

188
00:09:42,730 --> 00:09:43,720
Gracia!

189
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:46,280
Honey, <i>uma</i>—

190
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,260
<i>Uma</i>? [horse]

191
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:48,560
<i>Umareru</i>! [the baby's coming]

192
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,880
I-It can't be...! 
The due date isn't here yet!

193
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:54,660
Well, the baby wants to come out already.

194
00:09:54,660 --> 00:09:56,900
A doctor! 
We have to get to a doctor!

195
00:09:58,660 --> 00:10:00,470
Th-There's a blizzard!

196
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,000
In that case, I'll bring a doctor here!

197
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,250
Sit tight, Gracia!

198
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,230
J-Just a sec—

199
00:10:08,450 --> 00:10:11,170
Sorry about this, everyone.

200
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,800
Gracia-san, I brought some hot water!

201
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:17,050
Thank you. 
Set it there on the floor.

202
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:18,400
Wh-What else?

203
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:21,430
Let' see... I suppose 
we'll need a lot of towels.

204
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:23,780
Towels, you say? All right!

205
00:10:35,250 --> 00:10:37,150
The doctor sure is taking a long time.

206
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:39,880
Yeah, with all this snow...

207
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:42,950
I can't take any more! I'm dying!

208
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:46,830
Brother! Gracia-san said she's going to die!

209
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:47,910
Sh-She couldn't be...!

210
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:54,040
She's not dead, is she?

211
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:54,040
Mama-san!

212
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,130
You idiot! She's just lost consciousness, right?!

213
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:58,160
But if you think about it like alchemy,

214
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:01,560
there's a considerable cost in creating a new life!

215
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,970
Childbirth isn't alchemy, you know!

216
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:09,980
Th-Thank goodness she's alive! Are you all right, Gracia-san?

217
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:16,520
Dammit, what should we do?!

218
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,700
How can there be nothing 
we can do at a time like this?!

219
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:20,320
Big Brother,

220
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:22,030
the water is cold.

221
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:25,030
Ah, okay.

222
00:11:28,450 --> 00:11:30,410
Brother! What did you just do?

223
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:31,830
N-Nothing...

224
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:34,950
N-Nothing? But where's the transmutation circle?!

225
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,720
Then how did the water get hot?

226
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:40,200
How would I know?! 
Must've been force of mind!

227
00:11:41,140 --> 00:11:43,840
Here it comes!

228
00:11:46,430 --> 00:11:48,930
What should we do?!

229
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:53,050
Isn't the doctor here yet?!

230
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:04,950
Outstanding! Outstanding, Gracia!

231
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,000
Thanks to everybody.

232
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:13,000
I'm really, really grateful.

233
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:16,200
W-We didn't do anything.

234
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:19,200
That's not true.

235
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,150
You stayed at my side.

236
00:12:32,950 --> 00:12:37,730
This alchemy stuff—turns out it wasn't any help at all, huh?

237
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:41,770
In contrast, mothers are 
something awesome, huh?

238
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:47,480
They can do something an alchemist wouldn't be able to do in a hundred years.

239
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,450
The same goes for our mother.

240
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,000
Al?

241
00:12:54,680 --> 00:13:01,000
I wonder if I was that warm and soft when I was born.

242
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,760
O-Of course you were!

243
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:05,670
Really?

244
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:22,230
After that, we became 
much more absorbed in alchemy.

245
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:26,270
It was all we could do, wishing to take back the bodies we were born with.

246
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,500
Come to think of it, Brother,

247
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:37,050
you heated that water before without using a transmutation circle, huh?

248
00:13:38,820 --> 00:13:41,960
Yeah. That situation was something out of the ordinary, though.

249
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:45,100
Even so, it was still 
incredible of you, Brother.

250
00:13:45,100 --> 00:13:46,780
